title: Germany set to add citizenship test questions about Jews and Israel
description: Those taking German citizenship tests could face questions including: What gives Germany its special responsibility for Israel? How is Holocaust denial punished in Germany?

title: Amid U.S.-Israeli strains, Pentagon pushes for a new approach in Gaza
description: Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin urged his Israeli counterpart, Yoav Gallant, to abandon plans for a major offensive in the southern Gaza city of Rafah.

title: FSB chief, citing no proof, blames Ukraine and U.S. in Moscow terror attack
description: Senior Russian officials  have presented an increasingly convoluted description of what happened at the Crocus City Hall concert venue where at least 139 people were killed.

title: Abortion pill at heart of Supreme Court ruling is approved in over 90 countries
description: Legal wrangling over abortion and mifepristone — most recently in a federal appeals court — places the U.S. on a different trajectory from the rest of the world.

title: U.K. High Court delays Julian Assange extradition pending U.S. assurances
description: The United States will have three weeks to send the High Court its assurances that Assange will receive the full protection of U.S. laws and not be subject to the death penalty.

title: What the U.N. cease-fire resolution means for Gaza and how countries voted
description: Legal experts said the resolution was significant, as was the U.S. decision to let it through — signalling the Biden administration is losing patience with Israel.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Israel’s Gallant in U.S.; Netanyahu axes planned delegation over U.N. resolution
description: The Israeli prime minister canceled a high-level delegation to Washington after the United States abstained from voting on a U.N. cease-fire resolution.

title: U.S. allows U.N. ceasefire vote, but it’s too late for many in Gaza
description: After using its veto to cover for Israel at the U.N. Security Council three times since Oct. 7, the United States allowed a ceasefire resolution to pass.

title: Biden-Netanyahu rift grows, as Israel cancels delegation visit
description: Administration officials insisted there was no U.S. policy change, while expressing disappointment in Israel’s abrupt move to cancel a high-level official trip.
